Congratulations! If you are reading this, it means that lurker has been
successfully installed on your computer.

Unless you have changed it, lurker will be located in these directories:
	database files -  @DBDIR_expand@
	documentation  -  @DATADIR_expand@/doc/@PACKAGE@/
	web directory  -  @WWWDIR_expand@
	web url        -  @urldir@
	pid file       -  @LOCALSTATEDIR_expand@/run/@PACKAGE@d.pid
	config file    -  @SYSCONFDIR_expand@/@PACKAGE@.conf

For the newest version of lurker, see <http://sourceforge.net/projects/lurker>
For support contact lurker-users@lists.sourceforge.net.

Debian .debs can be found in debian/sid
Redhat .rpms can be built with (rpm -ta lurker-@VERSION@.tar.gz)

Please contact Wesley W. Terpstra <wesley@terpstra.ca> if:
	you are interested in writing a FreeBSD port
	you are interested in making a MacOS fink package
(lurker should already build on these platforms)
